The paper focuses on the empirical comparison and analysis of four representative DL frameworks, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the runtime performance and accuracy of DL frameworks, which could be categorized under distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). Additionally, the paper mentions the resource consumption patterns and their performance implications, which could be related to computer vision (cs.CV), neural networks (cs.NE), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
